37
00:03:11,950 --> 00:03:17,787
=Episode 17=
(Every Family Has Its Struggles)

38
00:03:36,687 --> 00:03:38,127
Mom, it's me.

39
00:03:38,330 --> 00:03:38,960
I'm in Huanzhou.

40
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,090
The weather's getting cold.

41
00:03:40,090 --> 00:03:41,810
I brought you and Dad some warm clothes.

42
00:03:42,210 --> 00:03:44,180
Qingyu, who told you to come?

43
00:03:44,210 --> 00:03:45,930
I told you to wait it out
a little longer.

44
00:03:45,930 --> 00:03:46,770
Go back.

45
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,330
I'm right across from the hospital.

46
00:03:48,330 --> 00:03:49,880
I'll leave
after passing you the clothes.

47
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:51,210
It's only going to take a moment.

48
00:03:51,460 --> 00:03:52,280
Just go home.

49
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,490
Don't you dare come upstairs.

50
00:03:53,580 --> 00:03:54,610
Go home right now.

51
00:03:55,980 --> 00:03:57,020
Are you listening?

52
00:03:57,050 --> 00:03:57,860
Mom.

53
00:03:59,540 --> 00:04:00,180
Mom?

54
00:04:34,050 --> 00:04:34,900
Qiao Beiyu!

55
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:36,780
Qiao Beiyu!

56
00:04:50,860 --> 00:04:52,050
Aren't you sick?

57
00:04:52,050 --> 00:04:53,660
What are you doing here by yourself?

58
00:04:55,450 --> 00:04:57,570
Out in this freezing winter
without even a coat?

59
00:04:57,610 --> 00:04:59,780
Are you trying to get worse?

60
00:05:04,340 --> 00:05:05,220
Where's Mom and Dad?

61
00:05:05,220 --> 00:05:06,450
Do they know you're here?

62
00:05:11,445 --> 00:05:13,130
What is the deal with you?

63
00:05:13,130 --> 00:05:14,120
Mom and Dad haven't been

64
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:15,960
in Shunyun for months
because of your treatment.

65
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:18,570
There's no one to run the noodle shop,
so we don't have any income.

66
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:20,900
No one to deal with Yu
when he got into trouble in school.

67
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:22,880
I had to be there
for the parent-teacher interview.

68
00:05:23,610 --> 00:05:24,930
You're an adult.

69
00:05:24,930 --> 00:05:25,980
Be more mature.

70
00:05:25,980 --> 00:05:27,220
We're all worried about you.

71
00:05:27,220 --> 00:05:28,300
Be more considerate.

72
00:05:40,300 --> 00:05:41,100
Qing.

73
00:05:42,490 --> 00:05:44,570
I am a burden to our family

74
00:05:45,780 --> 00:05:47,660
and our parents.

75
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:50,180
You're right.

76
00:05:54,130 --> 00:05:56,300
I'll give you back your parents, okay?

77
00:06:00,180 --> 00:06:00,980
No.

78
00:06:02,740 --> 00:06:04,180
That's not okay at all.

79
00:06:21,860 --> 00:06:22,610
Money!

80
00:06:22,980 --> 00:06:24,300
You only care about money!

81
00:06:25,420 --> 00:06:27,740
I don't have any money!

82
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:28,980
Take my life if you will!

83
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:31,440
I'm not good enough for you
anymore, am I?

84
00:06:31,930 --> 00:06:34,130
You were glad to spend the money I made!

85
00:06:34,540 --> 00:06:36,130
What more do you want from me?

86
00:06:36,340 --> 00:06:37,050
Let go!

87
00:06:37,370 --> 00:06:38,780
Come out!

88
00:06:38,780 --> 00:06:39,420
Let me go!

89
00:06:39,420 --> 00:06:40,490
You forced my hand!

90
00:06:40,490 --> 00:06:40,900
Stop!

91
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:42,810
You're driving me to a dead end!

92
00:06:43,960 --> 00:06:44,370
Come here!

93
00:06:44,370 --> 00:06:45,360
I can't live like this!

94
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,660
We might as well both die now!

95
00:06:47,050 --> 00:06:47,780
Die!

96
00:06:47,780 --> 00:06:48,780
No!

97
00:06:49,050 --> 00:06:49,370
Die!

98
00:06:49,370 --> 00:06:50,100
Help!

99
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:51,570
Don't touch my mother!

100
00:06:51,570 --> 00:06:52,370
Let go!

101
00:06:52,810 --> 00:06:59,660
Mumu! Mumu! Mumu...

102
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:02,900
Help her up! Quick!

103
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:03,370
Mumu!

104
00:07:03,370 --> 00:07:04,540
I'm sorry, Mumu!

105
00:07:04,540 --> 00:07:05,300
I'm sorry...

106
00:07:05,780 --> 00:07:07,180
I'm sorry, Mumu...

107
00:07:18,930 --> 00:07:19,810
Thanks.

108
00:07:22,130 --> 00:07:23,220
Does your foot still hurt?

109
00:07:24,370 --> 00:07:25,180
It does.

110
00:07:25,810 --> 00:07:27,130
But it was worth it.

111
00:07:27,420 --> 00:07:29,370
My dad got me injured,

112
00:07:29,740 --> 00:07:31,010
so my mom got into a huge fight

113
00:07:31,010 --> 00:07:32,660
with him over that.

114
00:07:32,930 --> 00:07:34,860
I think that actually
knocked some sense into him.

115
00:07:34,860 --> 00:07:36,660
He promised to quit drinking.

116
00:07:38,780 --> 00:07:41,810
For the first time in a long while,
we had breakfast together.

117
00:07:42,370 --> 00:07:44,540
I guess that's one silver lining.

118
00:07:44,660 --> 00:07:45,860
Bah, knock on wood.

119
00:07:46,690 --> 00:07:47,420
Mumu!

120
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,980
The disaster relief charity performance
is tomorrow.

121
00:07:50,050 --> 00:07:52,300
What are we going to do
without our lead dancer?

122
00:07:54,610 --> 00:07:55,570
That's right. Qingyu,

123
00:07:55,610 --> 00:07:57,780
you're a great dancer
and you know the routine well.

124
00:07:57,780 --> 00:07:59,490
Why don't you take Mumu's place?

125
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:00,660
I can't do it.

126
00:08:00,660 --> 00:08:01,900
Just give it a chance.

127
00:08:02,010 --> 00:08:03,340
Tomorrow's performance

128
00:08:03,340 --> 00:08:05,100
will be our last show

129
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:06,610
before we graduate.

130
00:08:06,780 --> 00:08:08,740
It'd be a shame if it went badly.

131
00:08:08,740 --> 00:08:10,570
You wouldn't want Mumu's hard work

132
00:08:10,570 --> 00:08:12,100
to go down the drain, right?

133
00:08:16,610 --> 00:08:17,340
That's enough.

134
00:08:17,370 --> 00:08:18,780
Don't pressure Qingyu.

135
00:08:27,810 --> 00:08:29,860
Okay, okay.

136
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:31,220
I'm heading out now.

137
00:08:33,330 --> 00:08:34,730
Is the shop shorthanded?

138
00:08:36,050 --> 00:08:36,930
You're lucky.

139
00:08:36,930 --> 00:08:38,300
You don't have to do a thing.

140
00:08:38,330 --> 00:08:40,260
I only come home twice a week,

141
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:41,900
and I still have
to get called in for work.

142
00:08:54,210 --> 00:08:55,380
Hm? Where's my key?

143
00:08:55,850 --> 00:08:56,970
Might be on the sofa.

144
00:08:57,420 --> 00:08:59,090
No, I remember I put it in my bag.

145
00:09:07,210 --> 00:09:08,850
Did you see the key, Qingyu?

146
00:09:08,850 --> 00:09:10,930
Dawdle any longer
and Mom will talk your ear off.

147
00:09:14,020 --> 00:09:15,420
I won't lock the door, then.

148
00:09:15,780 --> 00:09:16,900
Stay home and behave.

149
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:17,690
Don't go out.

150
00:09:17,690 --> 00:09:19,050
Got it. You're such a nag.

151
00:10:00,810 --> 00:10:01,780
(That's right. Qingyu,)

152
00:10:02,020 --> 00:10:04,090
(Tomorrow's
disaster relief charity performance)

153
00:10:04,090 --> 00:10:06,620
(will be our last show
before we graduate.)

154
00:10:06,780 --> 00:10:08,660
(You wouldn't want Mumu's hard work)

155
00:10:08,660 --> 00:10:10,020
(to go down the drain, right?)

156
00:10:10,020 --> 00:10:14,140
(Pinky swear.
Never break the promise in 100 years.)

157
00:10:27,930 --> 00:10:28,900
Come on, Qing.

158
00:10:29,620 --> 00:10:30,810
Put this hand up.

159
00:10:32,380 --> 00:10:33,730
Raise both arms.

160
00:10:38,730 --> 00:10:40,690
You're amazing, Qing!

161
00:10:42,540 --> 00:10:43,660
Beiyu,

162
00:10:43,660 --> 00:10:44,730
when can I dance

163
00:10:44,730 --> 00:10:47,210
as good as you?

164
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:49,050
When you grow up,

165
00:10:49,050 --> 00:10:50,850
you'll dance even better than I do.

166
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:53,380
Okay. Wait until I grow up.

167
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:54,380
When I'm old enough,

168
00:10:54,380 --> 00:10:56,140
we'll dance together, okay?

169
00:10:56,210 --> 00:10:57,020
Okay.

170
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:57,540
Promise.

171
00:10:57,540 --> 00:10:57,900
Promise.

172
00:10:58,260 --> 00:11:02,260
Pinky swear.
Never break the promise in 100 years.

173
00:11:41,925 --> 00:11:43,600
(Disaster Is Heartless,
but Humanity Cares)

174
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:46,280
(Huanzhou City Binjiang District
Disaster Relief Charity Performance)

175
00:11:46,730 --> 00:11:48,140
Do we have to repeat the set

176
00:11:48,140 --> 00:11:49,240
before the lead solo

177
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:50,570
since we don't have a lead dancer?

178
00:11:50,570 --> 00:11:52,240
It might be too boring for the audience.

179
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:52,800
She's right.

180
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:53,970
We need the lead dancer

181
00:11:53,970 --> 00:11:55,690
to elevate the emotion in this scene.

182
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:56,660
Without a lead dancer,

183
00:11:56,660 --> 00:11:58,180
the whole performance will be so dull.

184
00:11:58,620 --> 00:12:00,760
Our mission
is to complete the performance.

185
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:01,810
The audience will forgive

186
00:12:01,810 --> 00:12:03,020
a small imperfection.

187
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:05,300
But that would be embarrassing.

188
00:12:05,660 --> 00:12:07,540
Mumu, let's forget it.

189
00:12:07,540 --> 00:12:08,570
We should quit now.

190
00:12:08,660 --> 00:12:10,210
Yes. We should just not perform.

191
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:14,180
Am I too late?

192
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:28,050
I thought we were playing basketball.

193
00:12:28,570 --> 00:12:30,180
Why are we watching a performance?

194
00:12:30,690 --> 00:12:32,260
It's on the way to the court anyway.

195
00:12:32,570 --> 00:12:33,640
Might as well take a break.

196
00:12:33,640 --> 00:12:34,640
Got a problem with that?

197
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:35,810
No?

198
00:12:36,380 --> 00:12:37,180
No.

199
00:12:45,180 --> 00:12:46,200
Thank you

200
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:48,720
to the ladies of Victory Street
for the spectacular performance.

201
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:50,500
Disasters are merciless,
but we are kind.

202
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:51,330
Don't be nervous.

203
00:12:51,450 --> 00:12:52,620
From this moment on,

204
00:12:52,690 --> 00:12:54,810
you're no longer
the Qiao Qingyu trapped in a cage.

205
00:12:54,810 --> 00:12:56,020
You're a bird in the sky.

206
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:57,300
Fly.

207
00:12:57,500 --> 00:13:00,090
Our students are concerned
about world events

208
00:13:00,090 --> 00:13:01,260
and the affected areas.

209
00:13:01,330 --> 00:13:03,020
Next, let us all enjoy

210
00:13:03,020 --> 00:13:05,090
the dance performance
by Huanzhou High School.

211
00:13:05,180 --> 00:13:07,260
"The Song of Youth."
Please give them a warm welcome.

212
00:13:09,690 --> 00:13:10,730
We're waiting.

213
00:13:10,730 --> 00:13:11,780
Shut up, will you?

214
00:13:11,780 --> 00:13:12,450
Okay, okay.

215
00:13:38,212 --> 00:13:42,100
♪Under the sunlight♪

216
00:13:42,100 --> 00:13:45,463
♪Birds take flight♪

217
00:13:45,525 --> 00:13:49,562
♪Raise me up, hold me high♪

218
00:13:49,637 --> 00:13:52,925
♪Only you♪

219
00:13:54,112 --> 00:13:58,525
♪During the dark night♪

220
00:13:58,525 --> 00:14:01,000
♪A guiding light♪

221
00:14:01,087 --> 00:14:03,262
♪Just like you♪

222
00:14:03,262 --> 00:14:08,112
♪Makes life turn bright♪

223
00:14:08,150 --> 00:14:13,412
♪Breaking free from darkness♪

224
00:14:13,487 --> 00:14:17,275
♪You gave me strength♪

225
00:14:17,275 --> 00:14:20,287
♪Running for truth♪

226
00:14:20,287 --> 00:14:25,000
♪I find my path♪

227
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:33,162
♪Drawing on the hope that you render me♪

228
00:14:33,262 --> 00:14:37,325
♪In this long journey♪

229
00:14:37,325 --> 00:14:39,825
♪I run on lightly♪

230
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:35,930
(I'll always be here)

231
00:15:36,300 --> 00:15:37,380
(when you turn back.)

232
00:16:03,850 --> 00:16:04,440
Slow down, Mom.

233
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:05,680
What's the commotion over there?

234
00:16:06,970 --> 00:16:12,210
- Great!
- Great!

235
00:16:17,090 --> 00:16:18,620
Is that your sister?

236
00:16:20,210 --> 00:16:20,900
No...

237
00:16:25,420 --> 00:16:26,380
Qiao Qingyu!

238
00:16:28,050 --> 00:16:28,540
Hey.

239
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:29,300
What's wrong?

240
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:30,780
My mom's here, Mumu. What do I do?

241
00:16:30,780 --> 00:16:32,300
She's here? Shoot!

242
00:16:35,330 --> 00:16:36,300
Did you see Qiao Qingyu?

243
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:37,660
What are you doing here, Mrs. Qiao?

244
00:16:37,660 --> 00:16:39,090
Did you come to watch our performance?

245
00:16:39,090 --> 00:16:39,680
Where's Qingyu?

246
00:16:39,680 --> 00:16:41,180
Qingyu? Why would she be here?

247
00:16:42,140 --> 00:16:42,810
Mumu.

248
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:44,540
Where is she?

249
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:46,810
What would she be doing here
of all places?

250
00:16:46,810 --> 00:16:48,240
You must be seeing things, Mrs. Qiao.

251
00:16:53,970 --> 00:16:55,090
I suppose I might be.

252
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:41,900
Qingyu.

253
00:18:43,690 --> 00:18:46,970
You were on that stage today,
weren't you?

254
00:18:49,490 --> 00:18:51,010
I knew it.

255
00:18:51,660 --> 00:18:52,450
Don't worry.

256
00:18:52,620 --> 00:18:54,770
I managed to convince Mom it wasn't you.

257
00:18:56,250 --> 00:18:57,060
Thanks.

258
00:19:02,770 --> 00:19:03,450
Qingyu,

259
00:19:04,930 --> 00:19:08,210
you danced beautifully.

260
00:19:09,290 --> 00:19:11,010
You were as good as Qiao Beiyu.

261
00:19:46,660 --> 00:19:47,530
Qingyu!

262
00:19:47,820 --> 00:19:48,660
Over here.

263
00:19:57,210 --> 00:19:58,420
Sit.

264
00:19:59,100 --> 00:20:00,730
Meixi saved a spot just for you.

265
00:20:00,730 --> 00:20:02,210
I didn't. Don't be silly.

266
00:20:04,180 --> 00:20:05,250
There are only three of us.

267
00:20:05,250 --> 00:20:06,860
Let's eat lunch together from now on.

268
00:20:06,930 --> 00:20:08,490
We can save a spot for you.

269
00:20:11,250 --> 00:20:12,060
Thanks.

270
00:20:14,450 --> 00:20:15,900
Let's put the past behind us.

271
00:20:16,380 --> 00:20:17,490
Let bygones be bygones.

272
00:20:18,180 --> 00:20:19,010
Got it.

273
00:20:19,620 --> 00:20:20,250
Qingyu.

274
00:20:20,250 --> 00:20:21,060
Let's check out

275
00:20:21,060 --> 00:20:22,580
the co-op store after this.

276
00:20:30,010 --> 00:20:30,900
That's the fatty part.

277
00:20:46,730 --> 00:20:48,730
- "How are you?"
- Very good.

278
00:20:49,010 --> 00:20:50,730
This is the real practice test

279
00:20:50,860 --> 00:20:52,010
for the French knowledge quiz

280
00:20:52,010 --> 00:20:53,010
and proficiency exam.

281
00:20:53,250 --> 00:20:54,930
We still have some time left.

282
00:20:54,930 --> 00:20:55,920
I'll leave it to you now.

283
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:57,100
Review the materials and see

284
00:20:57,100 --> 00:20:59,970
if there are any points from this lesson
that you don't understand.

285
00:21:06,210 --> 00:21:07,770
(Hao: Mr. Ming's case)

286
00:21:07,930 --> 00:21:09,340
(seems to have escalated.)

287
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:11,930
(I think you should check on your dad.)

288
00:21:13,325 --> 00:21:17,200
(Huanzhou People's Hospital,
Suspension Notice for Investigation)

289
00:21:33,860 --> 00:21:34,380
Make sure

290
00:21:34,380 --> 00:21:36,800
Bed No.3 doesn't eat
12 hours before surgery.

291
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:38,180
And the patient in Bed No.27...

292
00:21:38,180 --> 00:21:38,900
Ms. Yanqiu.

293
00:21:40,210 --> 00:21:41,970
I need to talk to you.

294
00:21:45,340 --> 00:21:46,060
Ms. Yanqiu.

295
00:21:47,140 --> 00:21:49,060
Did my dad really do
what people are saying?

296
00:21:49,690 --> 00:21:52,530
Did he risk someone's life
just for money?

297
00:21:58,730 --> 00:22:01,530
The patient was in the late stage
of her sickness.

298
00:22:01,530 --> 00:22:03,180
It was hilar cholangiocarcinoma.

299
00:22:03,970 --> 00:22:05,580
The risk of surgery was too high.

300
00:22:05,690 --> 00:22:06,620
She was already rejected

301
00:22:06,620 --> 00:22:08,360
by several hospitals
before she came to us.

302
00:22:08,490 --> 00:22:11,140
She and her husband knelt on the floor

303
00:22:11,620 --> 00:22:13,380
and begged your father to save her life.

304
00:22:14,100 --> 00:22:16,380
Your father accepted them
despite the objections.

305
00:22:17,210 --> 00:22:18,250
The surgery went smoothly.

306
00:22:18,730 --> 00:22:20,420
But there were complications afterward.

307
00:22:21,180 --> 00:22:22,660
To save the patient's life,

308
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:25,250
your father performed a second surgery.

309
00:22:27,450 --> 00:22:28,140
Sadly,

310
00:22:28,690 --> 00:22:30,180
she didn't make it.

311
00:22:32,860 --> 00:22:33,490
Then,

312
00:22:33,690 --> 00:22:36,250
the patient's in-laws
didn't want to foot the medical bill,

313
00:22:36,280 --> 00:22:38,380
so they blamed your father
for unnecessary health care.

314
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:41,010
The hospital suspended him
for further investigation.

315
00:22:47,620 --> 00:22:48,690
Was it worth it for him

316
00:22:49,450 --> 00:22:50,580
to do what he did?

317
00:22:53,820 --> 00:22:54,620
That's something

318
00:22:54,730 --> 00:22:55,970
only your father can answer.

319
00:22:57,930 --> 00:22:59,340
The Ming Qiuxin I know

320
00:23:00,490 --> 00:23:03,340
always quietly and resolutely

321
00:23:03,340 --> 00:23:04,900
does what he believes is right.

322
00:23:05,970 --> 00:23:08,530
Even if he is misunderstood or wronged,

323
00:23:09,450 --> 00:23:11,140
he won't find excuses or defend himself.

324
00:23:11,620 --> 00:23:12,820
He's like that at work

325
00:23:13,210 --> 00:23:15,140
and in life.

326
00:23:37,660 --> 00:23:38,290
Sheng?

327
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:40,490
What are you doing here?

328
00:23:41,530 --> 00:23:42,180
This is my home.

329
00:23:42,180 --> 00:23:43,380
I can come home, can't I?

330
00:23:43,450 --> 00:23:44,820
Of course.

331
00:23:45,240 --> 00:23:46,620
I just came back to grab something.

332
00:23:46,620 --> 00:23:47,880
I'll be out of here in a moment.

333
00:23:48,060 --> 00:23:48,450
I see.

334
00:23:50,860 --> 00:23:51,770
Your food is burning.

335
00:23:52,450 --> 00:23:52,970
Right.

336
00:24:03,237 --> 00:24:06,800
(FRA Handbook,
Undergraduate & Postgraduate)

337
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:16,712
(Université de Saint-Étienne,
Université d'Angers)

338
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:19,000
(Université Paul-Valéry-Montpellier,
Université de Paris)

339
00:24:35,250 --> 00:24:36,380
I've had some free time

340
00:24:36,530 --> 00:24:37,770
the past few days,

341
00:24:38,490 --> 00:24:40,210
so I did some research.

342
00:24:41,290 --> 00:24:42,140
Take a look.

343
00:24:42,180 --> 00:24:43,180
Take them with you

344
00:24:43,560 --> 00:24:44,490
if you find them useful.

345
00:24:52,420 --> 00:24:53,730
Have you eaten yet?

346
00:24:54,860 --> 00:24:55,970
Let's eat together.

347
00:24:56,930 --> 00:24:58,290
I learned a few new recipes.

348
00:24:58,290 --> 00:24:59,060
Try them.

349
00:25:02,770 --> 00:25:03,580
Sure.

350
00:25:04,820 --> 00:25:06,380
All right. Wait there.

351
00:25:17,660 --> 00:25:18,820
Business is slower today.

352
00:25:19,060 --> 00:25:21,420
Aunt Fanghao
wants you to do your homework,

353
00:25:21,420 --> 00:25:23,010
so she had me deliver dinner to you.

354
00:25:25,970 --> 00:25:27,010
Eat it while it's warm.

355
00:25:27,380 --> 00:25:28,380
What about you?

356
00:25:28,490 --> 00:25:29,420
I've already eaten.

357
00:25:36,420 --> 00:25:37,250
Qing.

358
00:25:37,420 --> 00:25:37,930
Yes?

359
00:25:38,770 --> 00:25:40,930
Have you heard about Jinrui?

360
00:25:43,100 --> 00:25:44,820
Jinrui and Bei's scandal

361
00:25:44,820 --> 00:25:46,140
reached his workplace.

362
00:25:46,450 --> 00:25:49,010
He resigned and disappeared.

363
00:25:49,010 --> 00:25:50,600
His parents are worried about him.

364
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:52,200
They're searching everywhere for him.

365
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:52,620
So what?

366
00:25:52,620 --> 00:25:53,970
He deserved everything.

367
00:25:57,660 --> 00:26:00,420
There's something your mother
wouldn't let me tell you,

368
00:26:00,730 --> 00:26:02,820
but I think you deserve to know.

369
00:26:03,970 --> 00:26:05,930
You wrecked Jinrui's marriage.

370
00:26:06,060 --> 00:26:07,580
His parents had no intention

371
00:26:07,580 --> 00:26:08,900
of letting you off easily.

372
00:26:08,970 --> 00:26:11,120
They threatened to go
to your school and make a scene,

373
00:26:11,120 --> 00:26:12,340
to get you expelled.

374
00:26:13,340 --> 00:26:14,340
But Jinrui warned them

375
00:26:14,530 --> 00:26:16,290
not to.

376
00:26:16,290 --> 00:26:18,010
They only backed off after that.

377
00:26:20,010 --> 00:26:20,900
Qing,

378
00:26:21,970 --> 00:26:24,930
I know he made some mistakes,

379
00:26:25,970 --> 00:26:28,140
but he isn't beyond redemption.

380
00:26:40,490 --> 00:26:41,290
Eat your food.

381
00:27:01,970 --> 00:27:04,860
Wang! Wang...

382
00:27:09,140 --> 00:27:10,820
We're his family. Can we go with him?

383
00:27:11,100 --> 00:27:11,820
Can we?

384
00:27:12,060 --> 00:27:13,060
Wang...

385
00:27:45,060 --> 00:27:46,290
Is Mumu not here?

386
00:27:46,530 --> 00:27:47,490
She took the day off.

387
00:27:47,490 --> 00:27:49,420
Family matters.

388
00:28:07,820 --> 00:28:08,490
Mom.

389
00:28:12,180 --> 00:28:13,860
What took you so long?

390
00:28:14,140 --> 00:28:15,450
Was class extended again?

391
00:28:17,290 --> 00:28:18,420
Here, eat something first.

392
00:28:20,250 --> 00:28:21,060
Um...

393
00:28:21,210 --> 00:28:22,450
Mumu's father is sick.

394
00:28:22,450 --> 00:28:23,770
I want to go check on him.

395
00:28:27,212 --> 00:28:31,300
(Huanzhou People's Hospital)

396
00:28:39,770 --> 00:28:40,930
Shut up!

397
00:28:50,210 --> 00:28:52,210
Mrs. Qiao. Qingyu. You're here.

398
00:28:53,900 --> 00:28:54,530
Mumu.

399
00:28:55,180 --> 00:28:57,380
We're here to visit your father.

400
00:28:58,580 --> 00:28:59,690
You must be hungry.

401
00:29:01,250 --> 00:29:01,970
Qingyu,

402
00:29:01,970 --> 00:29:03,730
you two go and eat.

403
00:29:04,660 --> 00:29:05,450
I'll stay.

404
00:29:14,490 --> 00:29:16,140
Have some noodles.

405
00:29:38,690 --> 00:29:40,660
My dad has terminal liver cancer.

406
00:29:41,970 --> 00:29:42,900
The doctor says

407
00:29:44,060 --> 00:29:45,340
he might have a few more years

408
00:29:45,480 --> 00:29:46,730
if he goes through chemotherapy.

409
00:29:47,450 --> 00:29:48,860
If he doesn't,

410
00:29:49,560 --> 00:29:50,860
he'll only have a few days left.

411
00:29:52,580 --> 00:29:55,660
When my dad would get drunk and violent,

412
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:57,860
I wished more than once in my heart

413
00:29:58,060 --> 00:29:59,730
that he would just die.

414
00:30:00,560 --> 00:30:02,140
But now that it's actually come to this,

415
00:30:04,770 --> 00:30:06,450
I don't know how to face it.

416
00:30:12,180 --> 00:30:13,010
These days,

417
00:30:13,420 --> 00:30:14,770
he seems like a different person.

418
00:30:15,100 --> 00:30:15,900
He said

419
00:30:16,490 --> 00:30:18,250
he should've taken
better care of himself.

420
00:30:19,820 --> 00:30:20,860
He's not afraid of pain.

421
00:30:21,080 --> 00:30:22,140
He wants the chemotherapy.

422
00:30:25,900 --> 00:30:27,180
But my mom said

423
00:30:29,420 --> 00:30:30,730
the chemotherapy won't cure him,

424
00:30:31,730 --> 00:30:33,530
and it's too expensive.

425
00:30:33,930 --> 00:30:35,730
We're already so deep in debt
to begin with.

426
00:30:37,970 --> 00:30:39,930
We can't afford
to take on any more debt...

427
00:30:43,530 --> 00:30:44,340
Qingyu...

428
00:30:49,210 --> 00:30:50,730
I'm going to lose my dad.

429
00:31:06,580 --> 00:31:07,620
What do I do?

430
00:31:16,620 --> 00:31:20,770
We visited Mumu's father at the hospital.

431
00:31:22,340 --> 00:31:23,530
It's terminal liver cancer.

432
00:31:24,380 --> 00:31:25,530
He can't even have surgery.

433
00:31:26,250 --> 00:31:28,100
He won't be around for much longer.

434
00:31:28,900 --> 00:31:31,620
What about chemotherapy?

435
00:31:33,620 --> 00:31:35,380
Each session costs tens of thousands.

436
00:31:36,770 --> 00:31:38,100
Ordinary people can't afford that.

437
00:31:39,560 --> 00:31:40,770
If you get a disease like this,

438
00:31:41,160 --> 00:31:42,490
you just have to accept your fate.

439
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:45,060
Spending money on it is just
tossing it into a bottomless pit.

440
00:31:46,140 --> 00:31:47,180
Makes sense.

441
00:31:47,380 --> 00:31:48,250
In the end,

442
00:31:49,250 --> 00:31:50,840
the money's gone, the person's gone,

443
00:31:50,840 --> 00:31:52,580
and the whole family ends up
drowning in debt.

444
00:31:52,970 --> 00:31:54,140
How pitiful.

445
00:31:55,010 --> 00:31:56,580
If I ever get that sick,

446
00:31:57,010 --> 00:31:58,450
don't you dare get me treated.

447
00:32:01,860 --> 00:32:02,970
You'd better not get sick.

448
00:32:03,970 --> 00:32:06,900
Just use this to massage yourself

449
00:32:08,380 --> 00:32:09,250
here.

450
00:32:10,180 --> 00:32:11,140
It's good for you.

451
00:32:11,180 --> 00:32:11,440
Don't.

452
00:32:11,440 --> 00:32:14,160
They say this part of your body
is connected to your vital organs.

453
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:15,580
The spleen, the stomach,

454
00:32:16,010 --> 00:32:18,140
and all that.

455
00:32:18,690 --> 00:32:19,580
I'm busy.

456
00:32:45,950 --> 00:32:48,050
(Baidu, Medical Dispute Mediation)

457
00:32:53,320 --> 00:32:55,120
(Medical Dispute Mediation,
Difficulty Resolving)

458
00:32:55,120 --> 00:32:56,437
(How to Handle Medical Disputes)

459
00:32:59,075 --> 00:33:01,840
(Improve the quality of medical professionals
and establish good service attitudes.)

460
00:33:09,687 --> 00:33:13,537
(Blessed)

461
00:33:17,930 --> 00:33:19,010
Have you heard

462
00:33:19,450 --> 00:33:20,970
about Wang from Block 38?

463
00:33:22,180 --> 00:33:22,970
What about him?

464
00:33:23,060 --> 00:33:24,180
The drunkard.

465
00:33:24,180 --> 00:33:24,820
He's sick.

466
00:33:25,210 --> 00:33:25,900
Liver cancer.

467
00:33:26,140 --> 00:33:27,250
No way!

468
00:33:27,250 --> 00:33:27,770
Yes way.

469
00:33:27,770 --> 00:33:30,690
He doesn't look that old.

470
00:33:31,060 --> 00:33:32,660
How did he get sick?

471
00:33:33,060 --> 00:33:34,140
Guess what?

472
00:33:34,450 --> 00:33:36,860
The moment he was diagnosed,

473
00:33:36,860 --> 00:33:38,660
his wife made the statement.

474
00:33:39,340 --> 00:33:40,580
She won't pay for the treatment.

475
00:33:40,920 --> 00:33:42,290
We're talking about life and death.

476
00:33:42,290 --> 00:33:43,920
Is she seriously just going
to let him die?

477
00:33:43,920 --> 00:33:45,620
She has her reasons.

478
00:33:46,720 --> 00:33:47,180
Shopkeeper.

479
00:33:47,180 --> 00:33:47,730
Welcome.

480
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:48,900
She's here.

481
00:33:48,900 --> 00:33:50,240
A bowl of plain noodles for here

482
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:52,080
and a bowl of pork chop noodles
for takeaway.

483
00:33:52,080 --> 00:33:52,900
Use this.

484
00:33:52,900 --> 00:33:53,770
Got it.

485
00:33:53,770 --> 00:33:54,380
Thanks.

486
00:33:54,380 --> 00:33:56,140
Have a seat.

487
00:33:58,490 --> 00:33:59,380
This is a quiet spot.

488
00:34:00,360 --> 00:34:01,250
I'll be right with you.

489
00:34:03,440 --> 00:34:04,860
Plain noodles and pork chop noodles.

490
00:34:13,290 --> 00:34:14,460
Your plain noodles.

491
00:34:15,770 --> 00:34:16,250
Here you go.

492
00:34:16,250 --> 00:34:16,800
Thank you.

493
00:34:16,800 --> 00:34:17,890
And your pork chop noodles.

494
00:34:19,060 --> 00:34:19,880
I didn't order that.

495
00:34:19,880 --> 00:34:21,100
It's on the house. You need it.

496
00:34:25,210 --> 00:34:26,370
Your health comes first.

497
00:34:53,175 --> 00:34:57,737
(Outpatient Department)

498
00:34:57,737 --> 00:35:02,950
(Red Ribbon Campus Tour,
Recruiting Volunteers)

499
00:35:06,580 --> 00:35:07,370
Ms. Le Fan.

500
00:35:07,460 --> 00:35:08,620
Let me help you.

501
00:35:12,660 --> 00:35:13,730
Red ribbon.

502
00:35:15,980 --> 00:35:16,980
Ms. Le Fan.

503
00:35:17,180 --> 00:35:18,460
Are you a volunteer too?

504
00:35:19,620 --> 00:35:20,210
Yes.

505
00:35:20,410 --> 00:35:21,500
I provide counseling

506
00:35:21,500 --> 00:35:22,850
to those who need it.

507
00:35:22,850 --> 00:35:25,250
To help them better integrate
into families and society.

508
00:35:25,250 --> 00:35:27,410
Are you interested?

509
00:35:30,330 --> 00:35:31,140
How about this?

510
00:35:31,810 --> 00:35:33,840
We have volunteer activities
every Saturday.

511
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:34,980
You're welcome to join us.

512
00:35:35,450 --> 00:35:38,237
(Hand in Hand, Raise the Red Ribbon.
Heart to Heart, Prevent Aids.)

513
00:35:38,237 --> 00:35:40,199
(Huanzhou Association of AIDS Prevention
and Control)

514
00:35:40,410 --> 00:35:41,690
Have you seen Wang Mumu?

515
00:35:41,940 --> 00:35:42,690
Wang Mumu!

516
00:35:43,500 --> 00:35:44,410
Yes?

517
00:35:44,540 --> 00:35:46,850
Your aunt called.
She wants you to hurry to the hospital.

518
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:52,437
(Wishing you good health.)

519
00:35:53,330 --> 00:35:54,730
You know

520
00:35:54,730 --> 00:35:56,140
our situation.

521
00:35:57,140 --> 00:35:58,660
My hands are tied.

522
00:36:00,100 --> 00:36:01,060
We know

523
00:36:01,060 --> 00:36:02,730
how tough things are for you guys.

524
00:36:02,730 --> 00:36:03,890
We've already discussed it

525
00:36:03,890 --> 00:36:05,410
on our way here.

526
00:36:05,410 --> 00:36:07,460
The two of us will lend you

527
00:36:07,580 --> 00:36:09,210
the money you need

528
00:36:09,250 --> 00:36:10,370
for our brother's treatment.

529
00:36:10,660 --> 00:36:12,980
Mumu has good grades.

530
00:36:13,020 --> 00:36:14,290
She'll be successful.

531
00:36:14,730 --> 00:36:15,330
Absolutely not.

532
00:36:16,180 --> 00:36:17,330
Mumu's just a child,

533
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:19,460
and you want her to carry
her father's debts.

534
00:36:19,520 --> 00:36:20,370
I won't agree to this.

535
00:36:20,370 --> 00:36:21,850
You refused all the solutions!

536
00:36:21,850 --> 00:36:23,410
What do you want, then?

537
00:36:23,660 --> 00:36:25,660
Do you want my son to die? Is that it?

538
00:36:25,690 --> 00:36:27,810
We're here to solve this problem.

539
00:36:27,810 --> 00:36:28,660
We're a family.

540
00:36:28,660 --> 00:36:30,460
I won't drag Mumu into this.

541
00:36:31,290 --> 00:36:33,100
We're not going ahead
with the treatment.

542
00:36:33,540 --> 00:36:35,180
If anything happens to your son,

543
00:36:35,180 --> 00:36:36,180
I'll follow suit.

544
00:36:36,370 --> 00:36:38,370
How can you be so heartless?

545
00:36:38,690 --> 00:36:40,180
What's wrong with you?

546
00:36:41,600 --> 00:36:42,540
You've lost your senses!

547
00:36:42,560 --> 00:36:43,730
What's all this ruckus about?

548
00:36:45,940 --> 00:36:46,810
This is a hospital.

549
00:36:47,020 --> 00:36:48,020
Fight somewhere else.

550
00:36:49,660 --> 00:36:51,290
Sorry. We'll keep it down.

551
00:36:51,770 --> 00:36:52,810
It's all right.

552
00:36:53,330 --> 00:36:54,940
We can fix this.

553
00:37:04,890 --> 00:37:05,580
Mumu.

554
00:37:07,730 --> 00:37:11,140
I've been reminiscing a lot lately.

555
00:37:13,500 --> 00:37:14,660
You were so little back then.

556
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:17,890
Every year on the 15th day
of the first lunar month,

557
00:37:18,620 --> 00:37:20,210
you, me,

558
00:37:21,020 --> 00:37:22,100
and your mother

559
00:37:23,210 --> 00:37:26,180
would go
to the lantern festival together.

560
00:37:28,330 --> 00:37:30,020
You were always a smart girl.

561
00:37:31,730 --> 00:37:33,330
You'd say you were tired after a while.

562
00:37:34,040 --> 00:37:35,330
You'd reach out your little hands

563
00:37:35,770 --> 00:37:36,940
and try to grab me.

564
00:37:37,210 --> 00:37:38,460
You wanted me to carry you.

565
00:37:39,140 --> 00:37:40,730
You wanted to ride on my shoulders.

566
00:37:45,580 --> 00:37:46,370
We used

567
00:37:47,690 --> 00:37:50,020
to be

568
00:37:50,770 --> 00:37:52,060
such a happy family.

569
00:37:53,540 --> 00:37:54,620
Remember?

570
00:37:58,180 --> 00:37:59,060
Yeah.

571
00:38:01,060 --> 00:38:01,850
I know.

572
00:38:03,620 --> 00:38:05,620
I've made too many mistakes
over the years.

573
00:38:07,250 --> 00:38:08,460
I've let you down.

574
00:38:09,460 --> 00:38:10,620
I've let your mother down.

575
00:38:12,410 --> 00:38:13,460
I deserve to get sick.

576
00:38:15,660 --> 00:38:16,850
I had it coming.

577
00:38:21,500 --> 00:38:23,460
But I'm dying.

578
00:38:28,660 --> 00:38:30,100
I don't want to leave you two.

579
00:38:32,730 --> 00:38:33,460
Mumu...

580
00:38:35,940 --> 00:38:38,210
I want to see you go to college.

581
00:38:40,120 --> 00:38:41,620
I want to be there for your first job.

582
00:38:42,810 --> 00:38:44,810
I want to see you get married
and start a family...

583
00:38:55,940 --> 00:38:57,850
But we can't afford the treatment.

584
00:38:59,770 --> 00:39:02,210
I can't drag you and your mother
down any further.

585
00:39:02,290 --> 00:39:04,330
I'm sorry for everything, Mumu.

586
00:39:05,210 --> 00:39:06,940
I was wrong.

587
00:39:07,140 --> 00:39:07,850
If...

588
00:39:07,850 --> 00:39:09,690
If I could get another chance,

589
00:39:09,690 --> 00:39:12,060
I promise I'd do right
by you and your mother.

590
00:39:12,500 --> 00:39:13,210
Okay?

591
00:39:14,020 --> 00:39:14,810
Mumu...

592
00:39:18,730 --> 00:39:19,540
Mumu...

593
00:40:09,770 --> 00:40:10,330
Here you go.

594
00:40:10,580 --> 00:40:11,410
Thanks.

595
00:40:14,250 --> 00:40:16,100
You knew that family?

596
00:40:17,140 --> 00:40:20,660
They've been my neighbors
my entire life.

597
00:40:20,760 --> 00:40:22,330
They live across my grandfather's place.

598
00:40:25,690 --> 00:40:28,140
Was it the same with the patient
who begged my father

599
00:40:29,540 --> 00:40:30,410
to treat her?

600
00:40:38,180 --> 00:40:40,180
When a person's life reaches the end,

601
00:40:41,520 --> 00:40:42,770
their fate is often in the hands

602
00:40:42,770 --> 00:40:44,890
of their families and doctors.

603
00:40:46,580 --> 00:40:48,730
Their hope or despair
hangs on the decisions

604
00:40:49,690 --> 00:40:51,620
made by either of these parties.

605
00:40:53,810 --> 00:40:54,620
By the way,

606
00:40:55,140 --> 00:40:56,680
the mediation panel decided on a time.

607
00:40:56,680 --> 00:40:58,640
The investigation
of your father's medical dispute

608
00:40:58,640 --> 00:40:59,370
is next week.

609
00:40:59,770 --> 00:41:00,370
Okay.

610
00:41:01,810 --> 00:41:04,620
And the thing I asked you to look into?

611
00:41:05,770 --> 00:41:06,980
After Tan Qianqian's passing,

612
00:41:06,980 --> 00:41:08,440
her husband never showed up again.

613
00:41:08,440 --> 00:41:09,690
He won't answer our phone calls.

614
00:41:09,920 --> 00:41:12,060
Her great-aunt came and caused
some trouble a few times.

615
00:41:12,660 --> 00:41:14,140
They refused to pay the medical bill

616
00:41:14,140 --> 00:41:15,500
and demanded compensation.

617
00:41:16,040 --> 00:41:17,580
Your father's medical dispute mediation

618
00:41:17,690 --> 00:41:18,890
was their request.

619
00:41:19,660 --> 00:41:20,890
Did you try searching

620
00:41:20,890 --> 00:41:22,020
for Tan Qianqian's husband?

621
00:41:22,020 --> 00:41:23,770
We did, but we found nothing.

622
00:41:25,020 --> 00:41:25,890
There's something

623
00:41:26,810 --> 00:41:28,060
that stood out.

624
00:41:29,180 --> 00:41:31,290
Our department received a pack of cash.

625
00:41:31,370 --> 00:41:33,690
It was designated as payment
for Tan Qianqian's bill.

626
00:41:34,290 --> 00:41:35,580
But we have no idea who sent it.

627
00:42:11,420 --> 00:42:13,640
♪Maybe♪

628
00:42:15,500 --> 00:42:20,900
♪The more I care,
the more I tread carefully♪

629
00:42:22,590 --> 00:42:27,940
♪Counting the distance between us♪

630
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:35,100
♪Just one step away from reaching♪

631
00:42:40,100 --> 00:42:42,390
♪The future♪

632
00:42:44,090 --> 00:42:49,710
♪Time will unveil this mystery♪

633
00:42:51,290 --> 00:42:56,650
♪Waiting is a silent promise♪

634
00:42:57,500 --> 00:43:03,810
♪But one that never expires♪

635
00:43:06,130 --> 00:43:11,180
♪Turns out, all my thoughts♪

636
00:43:11,280 --> 00:43:15,590
♪Spell your name♪

637
00:43:15,880 --> 00:43:21,890
♪The one and only stubbornness
in my heart♪

638
00:43:22,110 --> 00:43:25,420
♪From the very first glance♪

639
00:43:25,770 --> 00:43:29,840
♪I started painting
what our future would look like♪

640
00:43:29,840 --> 00:43:36,110
♪That's when the dream began
to feel real♪

641
00:43:36,110 --> 00:43:39,770
♪Turns out♪

642
00:43:40,090 --> 00:43:44,150
♪Your heart had a place for me too♪

643
00:43:44,550 --> 00:43:50,530
♪Cradling the same story we both knew♪

644
00:43:50,800 --> 00:43:54,460
♪Thankfully, we were naïve enough♪

645
00:43:54,460 --> 00:43:58,000
♪And brave just in time♪

646
00:43:58,000 --> 00:44:04,980
♪To make sure our moments
weren't lost to time♪
